Description: The Cardiac Electrophysiology Ontology contains terms describing single-channel electrophysiological experiments and data obtained using voltage-clamp- current clamp and fluorescence imaging techniques applied at the cell level and multi-channel fluorescence imaging techniques applied at the cell- tissue and whole heart levels.
Authors: Name: BioPortal project on behalf of ontology owner.; Email:support@bioontology.org
